Brighton and Milton Keynes offices respectively. Those offices are to
close as the branch network is streamlined.
The other director to resign was Mr Stephen Denford, in charge of 3i's
Southampton office, which will remain open.  The three resignations
leave 3i with a total of 26 directors responsible for UK investments.
The senior decision-making body at 3i is its six-strong executive committee.
The cost-cutting programme announced in October involved the closure of five
of 3i's 22 regional offices and the shedding of 100 jobs.
3i has been forced to postpone public flotation several times in recent
months because of the recession.
