retailer, argued in a written submission that eco-audits should be mandatory
for British companies but not extended to local authorities.
The EC's eco-audit proposals have already been diluted, and would offer
voluntary guidelines which companies could use to govern scrutiny of the
environmental impact of individual sites.
Mr Wheeler said the British government was attempting to extend the
requirement to local authorities, a move which risked turning it into 'a
completely nebulous directive'.
