its markets, but the result would still be 'satisfactory'.
Sales would probably grow 9 per cent to SFr55m (Dollars 38.22m) this year.
In the first 10 months, sales were up 8.3 per cent to SFr44.3bn, but volume
growth, which was running at 3 per cent in the first half, slumped to 2.3
per cent in the 10 months, mainly due to a steep decline in sales in Brazil.
The Swiss franc's rise against most other currencies eliminated foreign
exchange gains. Source Perrier, consolidated since July 1, contributed
SFr800m in the four months to October 31.
