auction did quite well, totalling Pounds 514,217 with 17 per cent unsold in
the morning session. Russian art has been in deep recession for the last two
years.
Christie's experienced mixed fortunes with its sale of clocks and watches.
It totalled Pounds 649,385 but was 33 per cent unsold.
