   By PAUL ABRAHAMS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
UPJOHN, the US pharmaceuticals group, and Boehringer Ingelheim of Germany,
have agreed to develop and market four compounds discovered by the German
drugs group.
The compounds are all designed to treat central nervous system disorders in
which Upjohn has considerable expertise.
By co-developing the products with Upjohn, Boehringer will increase the
likelihood and speed of licensing in the US, the world's largest market.
